### WatcherNet — Demo HTTP Requests
### Run WatcherNet.AppHost first, then check the Aspire dashboard for the API's port.
### Replace {{api_url}} with the actual URL shown in the dashboard (e.g. http://localhost:5241)

@api_url = http://localhost:5241

### 1. Seed the system with iconic Buffy encounters (run this first)
POST {{api_url}}/encounters/seed

###

### 2. Check the Watchers Council global summary
GET {{api_url}}/council/summary

###

### 3. Get Buffy's individual combat record
GET {{api_url}}/slayers/Buffy

###

### 4. Get Faith's record (compare her "Escaped" rate — she's more reckless)
GET {{api_url}}/slayers/Faith

###

### 5. Check the Sunnydale Hellmouth threat level
GET {{api_url}}/hellmouths/Sunnydale

###

### 6. Check Cleveland — quieter but still active
GET {{api_url}}/hellmouths/Cleveland

###

### 7. Vampire threat category — most common by far
GET {{api_url}}/threats/Vampire

###

### 8. Log a single new encounter manually
POST {{api_url}}/encounters
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "slayer": "Buffy",
  "location": "Sunnydale",
  "creature": "Vampire",
  "outcome": "Dusted"
}

###

### 9. Spike gets a soul and becomes a slayer ally — add a surprise entry
POST {{api_url}}/encounters
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "slayer": "Spike",
  "location": "Sunnydale",
  "creature": "Demon",
  "outcome": "Dusted"
}

###

### 10. Re-check the Council summary — totals updated immediately
GET {{api_url}}/council/summary

###

### 11. Health check
GET {{api_url}}/health
